	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64937897"><p><div class="quote"><p>The summary mentions DRM as just another feature, but I'd guess it's the motivating one.</p></div><p>It's relevant, but probably not in the way you think. The Android security team doesn't care about DRM. However, existing DRM strategies have in the past <i>harmed</i> platform security, and one of the motivations for using VMs is to compartmentalize DRM to eliminate the risk.

</p><p>Currently, Android video DRM is implemented in ARM TrustZone on ARM devices (and all Android devices are ARM-based, to a first approximation). Several critical security features are also in TrustZone, notably the cryptographic services comp<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64937897">

